free_txt: .Corrections were made for multiple scattering,
for isotopic impurities, for neutron self-absorption,
for undetected events, for signal/background ratio -
all for different neutron energies
Karlsruhe 4PI-Ba-F2 detector consisting of
42 hexagonal and pentagonal crystals forming
a spherical Ba-F2 shell of 15 cm thickness and 10 cm
inner radius. Resolution is 7% at 2.5 MeV gamma
energy, peak efficiency  90 % at 1 MeV
3.75  MV Van de Graaff  Accelerator
pulse width is less than 1 ns, repetition rate
250 kHz, average beam current 1.7  microAmp
Metallic Li target of about 1 mg/cm2
.Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 keV
above the 7-Li(P,N)7-Be reaction threshold 1.881 MeV
giving neutrons in energy ranges 3-100, 3-225 keV
Flight path is 78.8 cm, resolution 0.5 ns/m
Single target irradiation
